      <section class="site-shell section" aria-labelledby="subscribers-heading">
        <div class="split-row">
          <div class="split-copy">
            <h2 id="subscribers-heading">Your users subscribe once. Support stops explaining outages.</h2>
            <p>
              Give customers one page with live component status and real uptime history. Anyone can subscribe by email, and every incident update you post reaches them without a support thread, with a one-click unsubscribe in every mail.
            </p>
            <p>
              The same updates ship as an RSS feed, so the customers who pipe status into their own tooling get it too. See <a href="/features/status-pages">status pages</a>.
            </p>
